selrach.bnetbuilder.model.variable
Class JunctionTree

java.lang.Object
  selrach.bnetbuilder.model.variable.JunctionTree

public class JunctionTree
extends java.lang.Object

Represents a junction tree slice in the dynamic network. Each JunctionTree is an instantiation of the original JunctionTree specified by the template graph variables.

Author:
Charles Robertson

push

public static void push(TransientClique child,
                        TransientClique parent,
                        java.util.Map<java.lang.String,TransientVariable> pushVariables)
                 throws java.lang.Exception
This pushes the potential's distribution into a higher clique, useful if we need the condition that there can be no continuous "tail" variables in a distribution, if we push enough times we end up in the strong root and by definition it has no "tail" variables

Parameters:
child - the child clique, who we are pushing from
parent - the parent clique, who we are pushing to
pushVariables - the set of variables we are pushing from U to W, must be a subset of U
Throws:
java.lang.Exception
